  "idea": "Add a final video available marker to shot groups in the video editor timeline. When a shot group has a final video (from shot_final_videos table), show a video icon badge on the right side of the shot group overlay (similar to stale variant amber badge). Clicking opens a panel with: 1) Switch to final video - removes all image clips in that shot group and replaces with a single final video clip spanning the same time range, 2) Dismiss reminder - hides the marker. Follow existing patterns: stale variant marker (useStaleVariants.ts, ClipAction.tsx), shot groups (useShotGroups.ts, TimelineCanvas.tsx), final video data (useShotFinalVideos.ts), asset registration (useAssetManagement.ts). Key replacement logic: register final video as asset, calculate time span of shot group clips, remove those clips, insert single final video clip, persist changes.",
